Title: LifeOS University Dashboard
Context: LifeOS desktop student and university management dashboard with a dark glass-morphism aesthetic.
Description of the screen: A desktop University Dashboard for LifeOS. Background is OLED Black (#050505). Left sidebar is glass navigation. Main header shows 'University' and 'Fall Semester 2025'. Top section features a 'Course Grid' with glass cards for 'Advanced Algorithms' (Grade: A-, Next: Exam Oct 30) and 'System Design' (Grade: B+, Next: Project Due Nov 2). Middle section is an 'Assignments' list with 'Read Chapter 4' (Algo) marked with a Study Orange (#f97316) high-priority flag, and 'Submit P-Set 3' (Math) due tomorrow. Bottom section shows a small weekly lecture schedule. A right panel displays 'Grade Analytics' with a GPA Trend line chart and a large 'Current GPA: 3.8' display. Typography is Inter, corners are Rounded 24px. Glass surfaces use rgba(24, 24, 27, 0.4).

Form factor: desktop

outputComponents.text:
The University Dashboard for LifeOS has been generated:

- **LifeOS University Dashboard**: A comprehensive academic hub that tracks course performance, upcoming assignments, and GPA trends. It uses Study Orange highlights for high-priority academic tasks and elegant glass-morphic cards to organize semester-long course data against the signature OLED black background.

Would you like to design a detailed "Course View" showing all syllabus items and notes, or perhaps an "Exam Prep" mode that integrates with the Focus Timer?

outputComponents.suggestion: Design a detailed "Course View" with syllabus and notes
Create an "Exam Prep" study mode interface
Design a "GPA Calculator" and academic planning tool
